snippet.textDisplay:
The only entertaining part of that number is when the confetti dropped, and that was lame. It reminded me of cats when they come out into the audience, I saw that as a kid when it came out as a Broadway show, and I hated it then. The biggest problem was that it was directed at the audience in attendance and not so much the viewers at home. It should be the other way around. That's the way Ricky Gervais hosts the golden globes, he directs his comments for the majority of the views not so much the insignificant audience in attendance.

The lady who sang the song is obviously very talented, but it was just a poorly choreographed number, and the song was dull, really a waste of a great talent.

Chris Rock and Steve Martin were very good, and it would have been much better to have just had them host and skip the musical stuff altogether. Especially in the light of how badly cats sucked, why would they do a number that was reminiscent of that crap? The Oscar's really drag on and it would be much better to tighten up the show by getting rid of this nonsense.

I don't hate musicals when they are good. The King and I, Phantom of the opera, showboat, even films like the blues brothers and many others have been done very well, but this was trash. To open the show with this was a huge let down.

That M&M guy was horrible as well, I could understand these numbers for a show like the Tony's but they really should get rid of these ridiculous musical numbers and speed up the show a bit. Or at least do music that's more universally appreciated by the audience. Save the rap and hip hop or whatever it's called for concerts and for shows where that's their target audience.

I feel sad for the winners who have the memory of their great win tainted by an awful show. The only Oscars show that might be worse was when James Franco and Anne Hathaway hosted, but that's a close call.
